      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "REVITALISE (2) has some solid form under his belt and proved too classy last time to win by one length at this track in a handy 22.25 beating Collinda Pops. Recorded one of the quickest times on the card in scoring last start. Looks the one to beat. SEATS TWO (3) was responsible for a modest effort most recently when fifth at this track over 390m behind Paw Harkonnen (22.69) in a Grade 5. Better than last start and can bounce back. CURDIEVALE RHODE (1) doesn't win out of turn. Finished in the minors latest when third (22.73) at this track and may be close to breaking through. Form from his last run is proving to be solid. Expected to be in this for a long way. GLIMMER OF HOPE (7) can sneak into the finish with the right run.",
